In your explorations you will find occasional rocks upon the surface of the world.  These rocks are indicators of ore veins in the vicinity.  More specifically:  If a nugget is present in a chunk, then an ore vein is also present in that chunk... or at least in the nearest chunks.  

While these indicators are useful, you can narrow down the location (and type) of that vein with the use of a Dowsing Rod or Prospector.  Simply right-click the face of any block, and you will learn what is behind that rock to a depth dependent on the quality of the tool.

You'd think exposing iron to air doesn't help it, but as always the trick is to just try more of it. Now emulating the raw power of a creeper with only air is yours, your pressuring advances force the iron to bend to your wishes.
The basis for all single-block machines in this era is the LV (Low Voltage) Machine Casing.

betterquesting:10.name:8: It's not as bad as it steams
betterquesting:10.desc:8: With better materials you are able to construct more reliable steam generation capabilities.
Your existing tools lack the subtlety for crafting wires.  Construct something with a bit more finesse.
Magnetized rods will form a core of several machines.  If you do not have a Polarizer yet, you can leverage some redstone to make the most basic type.
Get into the habit of using this recipe.  You will need many basic circuits.
There are several ways to assemble circuits, but for now you're limited to going via inefficient sources as red alloy.
Circuits (at this stage) require a considerable number of little fiddly bits.  An a lot of them.
In order to assemble your first rotor you will need to prepare several tiny tin parts.
Gregtech machines frequently require Rotors and Conveyors to operatore properly.
More complex components are required for more sophisticated machines.
You are just about ready to generate your first electricity leveraging the power of steam.
When a machine refuses to start properly, sometimes the right tool is required to encourage it.
While steam will most likely be your initial source of power, there are alternatives.
Feeling green?  If you are willing to invest in the infrastructure, you can construct more environmentally friendly power solutions.
Many chemical and centrifigual processes generate useful gases.  Some, such as Methane, can be burned for power.
Off the beaten (Gregtech) path are stranger methods of generating power.  Syngas can be burned for considerable efficiency.  If you can find a way to use the type of power it produces...
The coal boilers you've used thus far are very limited in output capacity and fuel types. These Large Boilers on the other hand can generate vast quantities of steam…if you're able to feed it.
Advanced Generators has a number of useful multiblock energy producing structures.  However, they do not produce "usefull" power directly.
You are finally at a point where you can construct a machine that produces metal sheets with "perfect" efficiency.
Batteries will enable you to carry power from place to place, and store it at higher densitities per cubic meter than steam.
Some particularly intricate containers require a canning machine to fill properly.
Electricity gives you the ability to seperate molecules themselves into their constituents.
The most popular batteries, Sodium batteries are easily to construct and fill due to the prevalence of salts. Notably, they are also the smallest capacity batteries.
They are somewhat unusual, but Cadmium batteries can be useful if you have excessive sources of rare earths.
If you have the means to extract Lithium, it makes for batteries with double the capacity of Sodium.
A battery buffer is your means of storing energy and buffering it for later use.  It can output amps equal to the number of batteries it houses.
For extremely intricate metal-joining work you will need a special tool.
The polarizer and wiremill allow you to create magnetized rods and wires much more efficiently.
Rounding out your resource-efficiency machines are the lathe, Extruder, and Cutting Machine.  Be mindful that some recipes require higher voltages than others.
Certain fluids and compounds can be solidified and mixed using the right machines.
Coke ovens allow you to improve the fuel efficiency of your coal.
By laying down a strong concrete floor you will be able to move around your factories with greater speed.
As your technology improves you'll be able to move items around with greater speed, efficiency and logistical capacity.
Your piping infrastructure can be improved further with logistical covers.
One of the most critical machines is the assembler.  It is the only way to assemble certain items, and is able to handle other recipes with greater efficiency than assembly by hand.
Many compounds cannot be created without specialized machinery, such as the Chemical Reactor.
To get started you'll need some basic resources.
You will need a considerable number of copper cables to progress into the next age.
Flint tools are an immediate improvement on your wood and stone alternatives
Mortars offer a more efficient means of producing Flint out of Gravel, and are required for some Dust recipes later on.
Crop sticks will allow you to mutate crops and improve their yields considerably.
A steady supply of food will be necessary to ensure your survival.
In order to determine the traits of your seeds you'll need a seed analyzer.

Time to hunt for some hives.  Be careful: bees get annoyed when you loiter around their hives, and get VERY annoyed when you break them.  You should try using a Smoker on a hive before breaking it with a Scoop.
Acquire more species for your breeding endeavours.
The forestry analyzer can scan bees and determine their exact traits.
Imperial and Industrial Bees are key to accessing useful resource-generating bees.

Better circuits require a whole different, dedicated circuit making branch of your industry.  While future advancements may open the gates for you to explore the wonderful world of circuitry, for now you are limited to limited manufacturing improvements. Specifically, you can now craft some of the components in an assembler for less than a half price. Use that for your advantage!
You'll need several varieties of ores in order to successfully progress to subsequent tiers.
Iron is necessary for any number of machines and tools. To get Iron, you'll first need to mine some Iron Ore.
There are a number of ways you can create torches.
Imagine that, flint & steel actually requires steel.  To start fires, you may need to assemble a more primitive tool; winding a rope around a stick to spin it quickly may do the trick.

Since you cannot cook logs in a furnace to make charcoal, your best option may be a Charcoal Pit. Charcoal Pits are comprised of wood piles surrounded by solid blocks. Note that some solid blocks yield better results than others.
Demonstrate your mastery of Charcoal Pits. And get rewarded.
You can extend the efficiency of your ores and yield important byproducts by washing, treating and centrifuging ores.

The first step towards better ore resource yields is producing crushed ores. At this stage your only option is to use a hard hammer (GregTech) to smash ores to pieces. The hard hammer has a nice ability to sometimes yield two crushed ores from one block.
Crushed ores can be processed further to get impure dusts.  With the right technology, impure dusts can be centrifuged for byproducts, some of which are rare.
To fill cauldrons and move fluids around, you'll need a bucket.
Impure dusts cannot be used in alloys. To cleanse the dusts, you can throw up to an entire stack of it onto a cauldron with water in it.
You'll need a considerable amount of clay to assemble your first fluid infastructure.

Clay Barrels are a primitive means of storing liquids. To build them you'll need Unfired Clay Barrels.  Smelt the Unfired Clay Barrel to acquire a Clay Barrel, where you can store liquid. These can be combined in a larger structure for more storage capacity.
Porcelain will require some Bone Meal.
Porcelain can be used to build Channels and Faucets, a primitive step above carting water around with buckets.
Channels and faucets are an early-game method to move fluids. You can set these up to transport water to, for example, near your Cauldron.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Right tool for the right job
betterquesting:10.desc:8: There are several tools which you will need to process resources, assemble tools and build machines.
You can significantly increase the duration of iron by cooking it again (as nuggets) into wrought iron.
Need an explosion?  You can craft some early-game explosives if necessary.
No Description
No Description
Show us that you can use the Object Submission Station
With the wrought iron you've acquired, you can greatly improve the durability of your tools.
Break down your copper and tin ores.
You can improve your ore processing yields considerably with Foundry equipment.
You do not have options to alloy Bronze very effectively at this point; you'll need to acquire some the inefficient way for now.
A modest improvement over Iron, you can improve you industry by smelting Bronze.
It is possible to greatly increase your resource yields by combining some industries together. For instance, machines from Integrated Dynamics and Foundry.
Smelt a goodly number of Iron Ingots. You will need them.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Explode me up before you go
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Almost all Pneumaticraft machinery and items require some amount of Compressed Iron.
The Pneumaticraft Compressor is necessary to generate the compressed air required by certain machines.
The small coal boiler is the most basic method of creating steam. It is reasonably efficient, but does not output very much.
Bronze pipes are a massive improvement over ceramic Channels for moving fluids.
An excellent way to generate infinite water is with Water Tanks. They will slowly yield water when water flows above them.
The most critical industrial multiblock and your primary objective, the Electric Blast Furnace will be required to acquire any number of resources.
Solar Boilers can be used to generate small amounts of steam essentially for free, so long as the sun is shining. Don't forget to clean them every so often.
Many materials and blocks can only be acquired by means of something like the Compressor.
The macerator is useful for 'mortaring' resources. Note that early versions (e.g. Steam) are NOT capable of duplicating ores!
Rubber will be very important for progressing into the next age.  It is most easily acquired by chopping down rubber trees.
Get the raw ingredients you'll need to produce proper rubber.
Diamonds can be difficult to find. If necessary, you can make them by compressing coal.
You can generate income by selling Diamonds.
In order to build wires you are going to need to acquire rubber, and a lot of it.
Many resources can only be generated in special machines. An alloy smelter is an efficient way to produce things like Bronze.

All microcrafting and no playing makes Jack a dull boy. 

Support a Jack in need, give him his very own worktable, capable of storing up to nine microcrafts to help all Jacks get to play.
Generating steam 'on need' can be inefficient. Storing it can ensure you have what you need when you need it.
You can generate income by selling Bronze.
Improve your smelting efficiency by building a Steam Furnace.
Compressing wrought iron yields a result which is even easier to work into steel, if you're willing to build the infrastruture for it.
At some point you will need to venture into this hellish landscape to acquire more unusual resources.
To progress any further, you will need to produce a new metal: Steel. You will need a great deal of it.
Produce a humongous quantity of Steel. You will need every ounce of it.
The first step towards assembling a proper sifting machines is acquiring a decent filter.
There are machines that can improve the yields of certain resources.
Now that you have an operational EBF, you have access not only to special resources, but also more efficient and quicker recipes for existing ones.
There are a number of special alloys that can only be created with the powerful heat behind the EBF.
In order to progress any further, you'll need to develop a metal which is both strong and lightweight.
There are numerous forms of energy in this world.  While they are all powerful, they are not always necessarily compatible...without the right tools.

You are able to build a large structure capable of holding significant volumes of liquid.  This structure can be comprised of any solid blocks so long as the Valve has access to the internal space.
The extractor is an efficient way of extracting resources from things like plantlife. This can save considerable time with, for instance, rubber.
Tanks can be somewhat underwhelming.  For a more significant investment of time and resources you can assemble something with a bit more volume.
The squeezer (essentially a confined box with a depression plate you can stand on) can function as a primitive means of extracting more resources from a given source.

Once you have achieved the power of Electricity, you can create a machine with sufficient torque to efficiently process ores for double the yield you would typically get.

Higher-tier Macerators additionally produce byproducts. It should be noted that higher-tiered machines tend to produce more of each chanced output. That includes the Macerator, the Sifting Machine, the Centrifuge and the Chemical Bath.
Emerge from your cave, brave the world, and discover the secrets of smelting.
For every risk, there is a reward.  For every gain, there is a price.
Take tentative steps towards comprehending deeper principals than what mere eyesight can reveal.
